parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become extremely difficult to turn or even lock up, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes extremely firm or locks up
the power steering warning light illuminates
the vehicle is difficult or impossible to steer
the steering wheel does not return to its normal position

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the loss of traction control, brake light issues, and speedometer malfunctions, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the loss of vital information, such as speed, fuel level, and warning signals, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: airbag light turns on and beeps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical power steering can cause the loss of power steering assist, which can lead to accidents or make the vehicle difficult to control.
The failure of the fuel level gauge can cause the driver to be unaware of the fuel level, which can lead to running out of fuel and causing accidents or stranding.
symptoms: Fuel level gauge does not work

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the BCM can cause issues with door locks, horn, and other electrical systems, which can lead to safety concerns and inconvenience.
The failure of the TIPM can cause the loss of various electrical systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: no warning or ability to avoid incident

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft and lifters can cause the engine to misfire, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents. It can also lead to costly repairs, including engine replacement.
symptoms: ticking or loud noise from the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold can cause exhaust gases to leak into the cabin, posing a safety risk to occupants. It can also lead to costly repairs.
symptoms: ticking or loud noise from the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and shutting off can cause accidents, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds. It can also lead to costly repairs.
